{"id": 231998576, "title": "Mnangagwa hails Putin as \u2018my dear friend\u2019 and ally", "text": "Reading Time: < 1 minute Zimbabwean President Emmerson Mnangagwa on Friday cast President Vladimir Putin as \u201cmy dear brother\u201d and said Russia was a consistent ally of Zimbabwe. Mnangagwa, speaking at the St Petersburg International Economic Forum, praised Putin for defending the independence and territorial integrity of Russia. \u201cZimbabwe considers the Russian Federation as a consistent global ally,\u201d Mnangagwa said on a stage shared by Putin in St Petersburg. \u201cStrength lies in our unity, adaptability and innovation. It is regrettable and unacceptable that the collective West continues to peruse hegemonic tendencies that blatantly violate the sovereign equality of nations, justice and fairness,\u201d Mnangagwa told the forum. Mnangagwa called for an end to sanctions on his own country that he said were imposed for the \u201ccrime\u201d of Zimbabwean people claiming their own land. Still Zimbabwe, he said, was \u201copen for business\u201d. Author Reuters View all posts", "summary": "President Emmerson Mnangagwa cast President Vladimir Putin as \"my dear brother\".", "url": "https://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/mnangagwa-hails-putin-as-my-dear-friend-and-ally/", "image": "https://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Putin-R.png", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 14:02:06", "author": "Reuters", "authors": ["Reuters"], "language": "en", "source_country": "za", "sentiment": 0.02}